Subject: categories: Re: Grothendieck toposes=0A=
=0A=
The very notion of Grothendieck topos involves in fact two topos=0A=
(sheaves over a site on the base). That is, it is a notion of geometric=0A=
morphism, it does not make sense as a single category.=0A=
=0A=
The notion of elementary topos is a completely different notion which=0A=
involves a single topos, it does perfect sense as a single category.=0A=
=0A=
This observation was made to me by Jacques Penon about 36 years ago.=0A=
=0A=
I agree with Joyal that the two notions should be kept apart. Not doing=0A=
so has created a lot of confusion.=0A=
=0A=
best  e.d.=0A=
=0A=

